attributes.title: A review of distribution and conservation status of Zamenis situla (Linnaeus, 1758) (Reptilia: Colubridae) in Bulgaria
attributes.description:
The leopard snake is one of the rarest snake species in Bulgaria. It is included
in the Red Data Book of Bulgaria as threatened species under high anthropogenic
pressure. Its distribution range in Bulgaria includes only three very distant regions in
the southern part of the country. Precise literature data about the leopard snake in
Bulgaria are scarce. The aim of this paper is to present distribution data as well as to
review the conservation status of the leopard snake in Bulgaria.

attributes.title: Figure 1 In A Molecular And Morphological Characterization Of Oliver'S Parrot Snake, Leptophis Coeruleodorsus (Squamata: Serpentes: Colubridae) With The Description Of A New Species From Tobago
attributes.description: FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic relationships within the Leptophis ahaetulla Group as inferred from 1,383 bp of mitochondrial DNA from the concatenated 16 S and cytochrome b genes. A 50 % majority rule consensus tree from the maximum likelihood analysis is shown. Values above nodes show the parsimony followed by the maximum likelihood bootstrap support values (only values over 50 % are shown). Leptophis coeruleodorsus sequences are indicated by the dark, vertical bar.
